#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an3.38"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.38:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.38:0.2"
msgid "4. Devadūtavagga "
msgstr "4. Messengers of the Gods "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.38:0.3"
msgid "38. Dutiyacatumahārājasutta "
msgstr "38. The Four Great Kings (2nd) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an3.38:1.1"
msgid "“Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo deve tāvatiṃse anunayamāno tāyaṃ velāyaṃ imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi: "
msgstr "“Once upon a time, mendicants, Sakka, lord of gods, guiding the gods of the Thirty-Three, recited this verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an3.38:2.1"
msgid "‘Cātuddasiṃ pañcadasiṃ, "
msgstr "‘Whoever wants to be like me "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.38:2.2"
msgid "yā ca pakkhassa aṭṭhamī; "
msgstr "would observe the sabbath "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.38:2.3"
msgid "Pāṭihāriyapakkhañca, "
msgstr "complete in all eight factors, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.38:2.4"
msgid "aṭṭhaṅgasusamāgataṃ; "
msgstr "on the fourteenth and the fifteenth days, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.38:2.5"
msgid "Uposathaṃ upavaseyya, "
msgstr "and the eighth day of the fortnight, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.38:2.6"
msgid "yopissa mādiso naro’ti. "
msgstr "as well as on the fortnightly special displays.’ "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an3.38:3.1"
msgid "Sā kho panesā, bhikkhave, sakkena devānamindena gāthā duggītā na sugītā dubbhāsitā na subhāsitā. "
msgstr "But that verse was poorly sung by Sakka, lord of gods, not well sung; poorly spoken, not well spoken. "

msgctxt "an3.38:3.2"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an3.38:3.3"
msgid "Sakko hi, bhikkhave, devānamindo aparimutto jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi, aparimutto dukkhasmāti vadāmi. "
msgstr "Because Sakka, lord of gods, is not exempt from rebirth, old age, and death, from sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress. He is not exempt from suffering, I say. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an3.38:4.1"
msgid "Yo ca kho so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu arahaṃ khīṇāsavo vusitavā katakaraṇīyo ohitabhāro anuppattasadattho parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojano sammadaññāvimutto, tassa kho etaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno kallaṃ vacanāya: "
msgstr "But for a mendicant who is perfected—with defilements ended, who has completed the spiritual journey, done what had to be done, laid down the burden, achieved their own true goal, utterly ended the fetters of rebirth, and is rightly freed through enlightenment—it is appropriate to say: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an3.38:5.1"
msgid "‘Cātuddasiṃ pañcadasiṃ, "
msgstr "‘Whoever wants to be like me "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.38:5.2"
msgid "yā ca pakkhassa aṭṭhamī; "
msgstr "would observe the sabbath, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.38:5.3"
msgid "Pāṭihāriyapakkhañca, "
msgstr "complete in all eight factors, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.38:5.4"
msgid "aṭṭhaṅgasusamāgataṃ; "
msgstr "on the fourteenth and the fifteenth days, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.38:5.5"
msgid "Uposathaṃ upavaseyya, "
msgstr "and the eighth day of the fortnight, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.38:5.6"
msgid "yopissa mādiso naro’ti. "
msgstr "as well as on the fortnightly special displays.’ "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.145, sc6
msgctxt "an3.38:6.1"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an3.38:6.2"
msgid "So hi, bhikkhave, bhikkhu parimutto jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi, parimutto dukkhasmāti vadāmī”ti. "
msgstr "Because that mendicant is exempt from rebirth, old age, and death, from sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress. He is exempt from suffering, I say.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.38:6.3"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
